					<h1>United Way Durham Region</h1>
				<article class="post"><h2 class="entry-title">"Designate Durham"  or "Give Where You Live" - The cornerstone of a better community</h2><img src="http://cdn.unitedwaydr.com/wp-content/uploads/Give-where-you-live-sign-resized.jpg" alt="" class="alignleft" /><p>“Give Where You Live” is at the core the United Way mission in Durham. We believe in the notion which has been espoused by many: Think globally, Act locally. Hunger, shelter, support for families in crisis or assistance with mental health issues. All can be accomplished here in Durham by “Designating Durham” and giving where you live.</p>
<p class="continue"><a href="http://unitedwaydr.com/give-where-you-live/">more <span class="noshow">about "Designate Durham"  or "Give Where You Live" - The cornerstone of a better community </span>...</a></p></article><article class="post"><h2 class="entry-title">Campaign 2015 - More than charitable - Building a better community...together!</h2><p>Helping those less fortunate is no longer a simple matter of charitable kindness or good will. In the 21st century it has become a strategic economic driver and a mark of a more prosperous and vibrant community. The rapid and dramatic nature of change and the local economic impacts of situations which began, often in other nations or on other continents, has created many and complex problems for communities. In these times a coordinated and multi factorial approach to community problem solving is more important than ever before.</p>
<p class="continue"><a href="http://unitedwaydr.com/campaign-2015/">more <span class="noshow">about Campaign 2015 - More than charitable - Building a better community...together! </span>...</a></p></article><article class="post"><h2 class="entry-title">75 Years of Service - A legacy we're proud to carry on.</h2><p>The 2015 Campaign for the United Way in Durham Region will mark the 75th anniversary of service for the United Way in this community. While much has changed in the past 75 years there are more than a few constants. Coming together as a community, in good times and in difficult times, to help those less advantaged is something we hope will never go out of fashion.</p>
<p class="continue"><a href="http://unitedwaydr.com/75-years-of-service/">more <span class="noshow">about 75 Years of Service - A legacy we're proud to carry on. </span>...</a></p></article><article class="post"><h2 class="entry-title">Homelessness Partnering Strategy 2014-2019</h2><p>United Way Durham Region is pleased to continue its role as Community Entity for the federal government’s Homelessness Partnering Strategy (HPS) funding initiative. HPS is a community-based program, to stabilize the lives of homeless individuals by providing direct support and funding to communities across Canada.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p class="continue"><a href="http://unitedwaydr.com/hps/">more <span class="noshow">about Homelessness Partnering Strategy 2014-2019 </span>...</a></p></article><article class="post"><h2 class="entry-title">12-12-12</h2><img src="http://cdn.unitedwaydr.com/wp-content/uploads/UnitedWayDurham-Metroland-Ad-DEC-FNL.jpg" alt="" class="alignleft" /><p>Do you want to give a gift which will keep giving for the next 12 months? Yes? Make a contribution of 12 dollars, pass it on to 12 friends, and you will know that for the next 12 months you will have helped make this a better community for everyone.</p>
<p class="continue"><a href="http://unitedwaydr.com/12-12-12/">more <span class="noshow">about 12-12-12 </span>...</a></p></article><article class="post"><h2 class="entry-title">Ride4UnitedWay Gran Fondo che i benefici 2015</h2><img src="http://cdn.unitedwaydr.com/wp-content/uploads/gran-fondo-4-colour-logo.jpg" alt="" class="alignleft" /><p>On <b>Aug. 16th 2015</b> hundreds of cyclists took to the road in Durham to enjoy not only a “great day on the bike” but additionally support agencies, programs and services which help many tens of thousands of people locally.</p>
<p>Proud to be a featured event in the inaugural Durham Festival!</p>
<p class="continue"><a href="http://unitedwaydr.com/r4uw2015/">more <span class="noshow">about Ride4UnitedWay Gran Fondo che i benefici 2015 </span>...</a></p></article><article class="post"><h2 class="entry-title">“A Great Day on The Bike” Ride4UnitedWay - In Durham Region</h2><img src="http://cdn.unitedwaydr.com/wp-content/uploads/gran-fondo-4-colour-logo.jpg" alt="" class="alignleft" /><p>As fall beckons, the leaves begin to change and we prepare for Thanksgiving, Halloween and the Holidays; cyclists of all ability, shapes and sizes must wait until 2016 to relive a great day on the bike had by all this past August. Almost 400 riders helped to raise just shy of fifty thousand dollars as they enjoyed riding their bike in Durham Region.</p>
<p class="continue"><a href="http://unitedwaydr.com/ride4unitedway2014/">more <span class="noshow">about “A Great Day on The Bike” Ride4UnitedWay - In Durham Region </span>...</a></p></article><article class="post"><h2 class="entry-title">Points4UnitedWay</h2><img src="http://cdn.unitedwaydr.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/generals-logo.jpg" alt="" class="alignleft" /><p>“Teaming up to build a better community” is at the core of why we were created more than 70 years ago. We are proud to be “Teaming up” with the Oshawa Generals, and particularly proud that Michael Dal Colle, Anthony Cirelli and Mitchell Vande Sompel will be scoring points on the ice and helping to build a better community for all as our “Scoring Ambassadors for the United Way”.</p>
<p class="continue"><a href="http://unitedwaydr.com/points4/">more <span class="noshow">about Points4UnitedWay </span>...</a></p></article><article class="post"><h2 class="entry-title">"Drive and Give"</h2><p>Pro Oil Change in Ajax is offering the &#8220;Drive and Give&#8221; Program.  For the Town of Ajax Employee&#8217;s 10% of their vehicle maintenance purchases at Pro Oil Change will be donated to the United Way Durham Region.</p>
<p class="continue"><a href="http://unitedwaydr.com/drive-give/">more <span class="noshow">about "Drive and Give" </span>...</a></p></article><article class="post"><h2 class="entry-title">Great Venue and Great Partnership</h2><p>The General Motors Centre has been host to big names such as Elton John, the Wiggles, The Tragically Hip and Marianas Trench, but it is also the place you can go to take in sporting events like the Oshawa Generals hockey games, Durham TurfDogs and more!</p>
<p class="continue"><a href="http://unitedwaydr.com/great-venue-and-great-partnership/">more <span class="noshow">about Great Venue and Great Partnership </span>...</a></p></article><article class="post"><h2 class="entry-title">73rd United Way Campaign In Durham Launched</h2><p>“Campaign for the Community”. Created in the depths of the Second World War, the predecessor to the current United Way was designed to coordinate a broad community wide effort to help those disadvantaged and most in need during the war. The concept was to help those who needed it in an efficient, effective and coordinated fashion. “The original idea, the notion that optimizing donor value in difficult times is the best way to help people is just as important, if not more so today, than perhaps at any time in our history”. There can be no doubt that we are all experiencing the impacts of the recent state of economic dislocation and rapid rate of change which has affected so many” says United Way Campaign Director, Robert Howard. “Bringing the entire community together in common cause is a positive response and a great way to help ensure the vitality and resilience of a community in these times”, he continues.</p>
<p class="continue"><a href="http://unitedwaydr.com/73rd-campaign-launched/">more <span class="noshow">about 73rd United Way Campaign In Durham Launched </span>...</a></p></article><article class="post"><h2 class="entry-title">Serving all of Durham Region</h2><p>The final steps in the process to create the United Way of Durham Region have now been completed. For more than 40 years there were two United Ways serving in Durham. (The United Way of Oshawa/Whitby was created 70 years ago. It later added the communities of Clarington and the townships of Brock &amp; Scugog) About 40 years ago the Ajax/Pickering United Way was formed, and Uxbridge was added a number of years ago. The Boards of both United Ways, working with the enthusiastic support of the United Way of Canada voted to take the necessary steps to form a single United Way.</p>
<p class="continue"><a href="http://unitedwaydr.com/serving-all-of-durham-region/">more <span class="noshow">about Serving all of Durham Region </span>...</a></p></article><article class="post"><h2 class="entry-title">"Thought of the day"</h2><p>A note to site visitors about the &#8220;thought of the day&#8221; on the top of this page.</p>
<p class="continue"><a href="http://unitedwaydr.com/a-note-to-site-visitors-about-the-thought-of-the-day-on-the-top-of-this-page/">more <span class="noshow">about "Thought of the day" </span>...</a></p></article>				</div> <!-- end #content -->
